<dl id="n35036c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35036c">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35036c"> 36(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 3legged mare / (gallows)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">DEADLY NEVERGREEN, that bears fruit all the year round. The gallows, or three-legged mare. <font color="green">[THREE-LEGGED MARE, or stool. The gallows, formerly consisting of three posts, over which were laid three transverse beams.]</font> <small> Captain Francis Grose, <a name="FGCD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FGCD"><cite title="source">A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue</cite></a> (1785) 00</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
